00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:15.360
- But the issue of suing Fox News

00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:16.920
or other cable news channels

00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:18.870
isn't exactly coming out of left field.

00:11:18.870 --> 00:11:20.880
And, as a result, some have argued

00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:23.610
that Fox News ought to face some liability

00:11:23.610 --> 00:11:27.480
for the misinformation that
they allegedly have circulated.

00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:29.570
And Fox News itself
appears to be concerned

00:11:29.570 --> 00:11:31.990
they may be subject to a
potential lawsuit form viewers

00:11:31.990 --> 00:11:34.490
for their misleading
reporting of the coronavirus.

00:11:34.490 --> 00:11:36.470
In fact, just recently
Fox Business Network

00:11:36.470 --> 00:11:38.090
parted ways with Trish Regan

00:11:38.090 --> 00:11:40.490
just a few days after she
made the bold declaration

00:11:40.490 --> 00:11:41.907
that the coronavirus was,

00:11:41.907 --> 00:11:44.340
"another attempt to
impeach the president."

00:11:44.340 --> 00:11:46.000
- And like with the Mueller investigation,

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:49.480
like with Ukrainegate, they
don't care who they hurt.

00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:53.830
- So if indeed their reporting
is misleading or false

00:11:53.830 --> 00:11:56.030
and with a bunch of viewers
that showed up a little late

00:11:56.030 --> 00:11:58.930
to the game having relied on
the message pushed by Fox News,

00:11:58.930 --> 00:12:02.060
could these viewers have a
cause of action against Fox News

00:12:02.060 --> 00:12:03.330
for injuries that they suffered

00:12:03.330 --> 00:12:05.250
as a result of the coronavirus?

00:12:05.250 --> 00:12:07.920
Well the initial answer is
they could probably file suit,

00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:09.180
but that doesn't necessarily mean

00:12:09.180 --> 00:12:10.730
that the suit would be successful.

00:12:10.730 --> 00:12:12.210
Probably quite the opposite.

00:12:12.210 --> 00:12:14.930
In theory, an individual
could bring a civil lawsuit

00:12:14.930 --> 00:12:16.930
against Fox News for committing an act

00:12:16.930 --> 00:12:19.620
or omission that gave
rise to an injury or harm

00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:21.770
for which the courts
could impose liability

00:12:21.770 --> 00:12:23.810
commonly known as a tort.

00:12:23.810 --> 00:12:25.240
The argument would most likely be

00:12:25.240 --> 00:12:26.930
that they breached a
duty to the plaintiffs

00:12:26.930 --> 00:12:29.510
in presenting them with false
or misleading information

00:12:29.510 --> 00:12:30.720
and that as a result of which

00:12:30.720 --> 00:12:32.950
the plaintiffs suffered
significant damages.

00:12:32.950 --> 00:12:35.050
Now we don't have time
to get into the nuance

00:12:35.050 --> 00:12:37.150
of every aspect of tort
law and civil litigation,

00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:39.150
but most likely a claim of this nature

00:12:39.150 --> 00:12:40.370
could be made by a plaintiff

00:12:40.370 --> 00:12:42.650
on the grounds of something
like public nuisance

00:12:42.650 --> 00:12:45.770
or maybe some form of
negligent misrepresentation.

00:12:45.770 --> 00:12:48.310
In a suit for public nuisance
the plaintiff can recover

00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:50.100
for activities that hurt a neighborhood

00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:52.040
or society as a whole.

00:12:52.040 --> 00:12:54.560
But to be liable for public
nuisance it must be proven

00:12:54.560 --> 00:12:57.110
that the defendant interfered
with public property

00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.780
or a right that is common to the public.

00:12:58.780 --> 00:12:59.930
But usually that's reserved

00:12:59.930 --> 00:13:02.810
for creating a public health hazard.

00:13:02.810 --> 00:13:04.900
Another argument could be
made for suing Fox News

00:13:04.900 --> 00:13:06.850
under a negligent
misrepresentation theory,

00:13:06.850 --> 00:13:08.960
although that's typically
seen in contract actions

00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:10.390
or quasi-contract actions

00:13:10.390 --> 00:13:13.530
where the main premise
of the misrepresentation

00:13:13.530 --> 00:13:14.830
has to do with a person's failure

00:13:14.830 --> 00:13:17.040
to exercise a reasonable duty of care

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:18.400
which in turn causes another person

00:13:18.400 --> 00:13:20.120
to be injured in some manner.

00:13:20.120 --> 00:13:23.080
Basically someone says
something that's false.

00:13:23.080 --> 00:13:25.120
They either knew it was false at the time,

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:26.700
or they should have known
it was false at the time,

00:13:26.700 --> 00:13:30.310
and as a result another person
detrimentally relies on that

00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.050
and incurs damages.

00:13:32.050 --> 00:13:34.860
But Fox News doesn't have
a contractual relationship

00:13:34.860 --> 00:13:38.170
with its viewers and doesn't
really have an obligation

00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.090
to do anything on behalf of its viewers

00:13:40.090 --> 00:13:41.930
including telling them the truth.

00:13:41.930 --> 00:13:44.410
Some states have consumer
protection statutes

00:13:44.410 --> 00:13:45.243
that might apply.

00:13:45.243 --> 00:13:47.330
For example, a consumer watchdog group

00:13:47.330 --> 00:13:49.060
called WASHLITE in Washington State

00:13:49.060 --> 00:13:52.080
filed a suit against Fox News
claiming its news coverage

00:13:52.080 --> 00:13:54.490
violated consumer protection statutes.

00:13:54.490 --> 00:13:56.300
That particular suit also alleged

00:13:56.300 --> 00:13:59.260
that Fox committed the tort of outrage

00:13:59.260 --> 00:14:00.910
which isn't really a thing.

00:14:00.910 --> 00:14:02.160
Sometimes that's a synonym

00:14:02.160 --> 00:14:04.840
for intentional infliction
of emotional distress,

00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:07.070
but that definitely doesn't apply here.

00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:10.320
So the first suit out of
the gate suing Fox News

00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:11.870
is pretty much nonsense

00:14:11.870 --> 00:14:15.380
and is absolutely going to get
dismissed very very quickly.

00:14:15.380 --> 00:14:18.540
In general throwing nonsensical
claims into a complaint

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:20.550
is not a good look, and
that doesn't bode well

00:14:20.550 --> 00:14:22.550
for the success of your lawsuit.

00:14:22.550 --> 00:14:24.730
Now despite having these plausible

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:27.070
and some not so plausible legal grounds

00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:29.660
to file suit against Fox News,
it's important to remember

00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.670
that the goal is not
just to file a lawsuit

00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:34.370
but actually to win and get damages.

00:14:34.370 --> 00:14:35.860
Now beyond the initial hurdles

00:14:35.860 --> 00:14:37.000
such as proving that a plaintiff

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:38.820
could establish justifiable reliance

00:14:38.820 --> 00:14:41.380
on information received
from a partisan news source,

00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:44.540
Fox News will have many
many defenses in its arsenal

00:14:44.540 --> 00:14:47.110
to probably get all of
these potential lawsuits

00:14:47.110 --> 00:14:48.750
dismissed pretty quickly.

00:14:48.750 --> 00:14:51.410
The first and strongest
defense for Fox News

00:14:51.410 --> 00:14:54.210
is probably free speech
under the First Amendment.

00:14:54.210 --> 00:14:56.970
You might not agree
with Fox News' message,

00:14:56.970 --> 00:14:59.590
but they have a First
Amendment right to say it,

00:14:59.590 --> 00:15:00.820
and they should.

00:15:00.820 --> 00:15:02.970
Now the framework for
the free speech defense

00:15:02.970 --> 00:15:05.210
starts with the seminal
case from the 1960s

00:15:05.210 --> 00:15:07.250
called New York Times versus Sullivan

00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:08.920
which held that the First Amendment's

00:15:08.920 --> 00:15:10.600
protections of free speech

00:15:10.600 --> 00:15:13.230
are not limited to just
truthful statements,

00:15:13.230 --> 00:15:15.807
because, "An erroneous
statement is inevitable

00:15:15.807 --> 00:15:18.447
"in free debate, and must be protected

00:15:18.447 --> 00:15:19.617
"if the freedoms of expression

00:15:19.617 --> 00:15:23.220
"are to have the breathing space
that they need to survive."

00:15:23.220 --> 00:15:24.410
Over the years this holding

00:15:24.410 --> 00:15:26.450
has led to a fairly bulletproof defense

00:15:26.450 --> 00:15:27.840
for all sorts of tort actions

00:15:27.840 --> 00:15:30.190
including those for product
liability, defamation,

00:15:30.190 --> 00:15:32.770
including those involving media outlets.

00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:34.070
Now I have covered the holding

00:15:34.070 --> 00:15:35.260
in New York Times versus Sullivan

00:15:35.260 --> 00:15:37.530
on this channel many times in the past.

00:15:37.530 --> 00:15:41.190
I'll probably do it again
because it is always relevant,

00:15:41.190 --> 00:15:45.030
but the idea is that we
shouldn't punish misleading

00:15:45.030 --> 00:15:47.520
or false speech in most cases.

00:15:47.520 --> 00:15:51.130
We should simply fight it
with more accurate speech.

00:15:51.130 --> 00:15:53.780
And we generally don't want
the government making decisions

00:15:53.780 --> 00:15:56.410
as to what speech is true
and what speech is false.

00:15:56.410 --> 00:16:00.927
- They are the fake, fake disgusting news.

00:16:00.927 --> 00:16:02.150
(crowd cheering)

00:16:02.150 --> 00:16:03.880
- That's a dangerous road to go down.

00:16:03.880 --> 00:16:06.760
Another defense would be the
lack of proximate causation.

00:16:06.760 --> 00:16:08.450
Fox News would probably argue

00:16:08.450 --> 00:16:11.900
that any plaintiff would
be unable to show that

00:16:11.900 --> 00:16:14.167
whatever the misleading
statements from Fox News

00:16:14.167 --> 00:16:19.120
was the actual proximate act
that led to their contracting

00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:23.230
of the coronavirus or
the economic downturn.

00:16:23.230 --> 00:16:24.760
There are lots of different factors

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:25.880
going on at any given time,

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:28.640
and it's unlikely that
Fox News contributed

00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:31.660
in the last instance to
the damages suffered.

00:16:31.660 --> 00:16:34.070
And another defense is that
Fox News would simply argue

00:16:34.070 --> 00:16:37.147
that they don't have a duty
to any of their viewers.

00:16:37.147 --> 00:16:38.910
There's not a special relationship

00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:41.610
that gives rise to any special duty.

00:16:41.610 --> 00:16:45.970
If you are walking by a pool
and you see someone drowning,

00:16:45.970 --> 00:16:48.350
generally speaking unless you
pushed them into the pool,

00:16:48.350 --> 00:16:50.440
you don't have a duty to pull them out.

00:16:50.440 --> 00:16:51.900
Now the no-duty rule,

00:16:51.900 --> 00:16:55.260
which has its origin in cases
involving property owners,

00:16:55.260 --> 00:16:57.420
generally holds that a
defendant owes no duty of care

00:16:57.420 --> 00:17:00.110
to warn, protect, or insure against risks

00:17:00.110 --> 00:17:02.200
that are common, frequent, or expected.

00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:03.033
And since Fox News

00:17:03.033 --> 00:17:05.110
doesn't have any particular
special relationship

00:17:05.110 --> 00:17:07.120
with any of its viewers,
it doesn't owe a duty

00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:08.640
and therefore can't be held liable

00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:10.430
for any kind of negligent acts.

00:17:10.430 --> 00:17:12.730
This is generally what
we call a SLAPP suit,

00:17:12.730 --> 00:17:14.560
or in other words a strategic lawsuit

00:17:14.560 --> 00:17:16.000
against public participation.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:18.670
